net.njcull.collections

Interface ArrayBackedMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this map
    V - the type of values maintained by this map
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImmutableArrayMap, ImmutableHashedArrayMap, ImmutableSortedArrayMap, ImmutableSortedArrayPropertyMap, ImmutableUniSortedArrayMap

    public interface ArrayBackedMap<K,V>
extends java.util.Map<K,V>

    A Map implemented by a backing array, with ArrayBackedSet and ArrayBackedCollection views over the data.

    Version:
    11/01/2016.

      • hashCode

        static <K,V> int hashCode(ArrayBackedMap<K,V> m)
        Returns the hash code value for this map. The hash code of a map is defined to be the sum of the hash codes of each entry in the map's entrySet() view. This ensures that m1.equals(m2) implies that m1.hashCode()==m2.hashCode() for any two maps m1 and m2, as required by the general contract of Object.hashCode().

        This implementation is handled as a static method rather than a default method because a default method cannot override any method of Object.

        Type Parameters:
        K - the type of keys in the map
        V - the type of values in the map
        Parameters:
        m - the map from which the hashcode will be generated
        Returns:
        the hash code value for this map

      • toString

        static <K,V> java.lang.String toString(ArrayBackedMap<K,V> m)
        Returns a string representation of this map. The string representation consists of a list of key-value mappings in the order returned by the map's entryAt indexer, enclosed in braces ("{}"). Adjacent mappings are separated by the characters ", " (comma and space). Each key-value mapping is rendered as the key followed by an equals sign ("=") followed by the associated value. Keys and values are converted to strings as by String.valueOf(Object).

        This implementation is handled as a static method rather than a default method because a default method cannot override any method of Object.

        Type Parameters:
        K - the type of keys in the map
        V - the type of values in the map
        Parameters:
        m - the map from which the string value will be generated
        Returns:
        a string representation of this map

      • forEach

        static <K,V> void forEach(ArrayBackedMap<K,V> m,
                          java.util.function.BiConsumer<? super K,? super V> action)
        Performs the given action for each entry in this map until all entries have been processed or the action throws an exception. Actions are performed in the order of its entryAt(int) method. Exceptions thrown by the action are relayed to the caller.

        This implementation is handled as a static method rather than a default method to avoid the diamond inheritance problem with default methods.

        Type Parameters:
        K - the type of keys in the map
        V - the type of values in the map
        Parameters:
        m - the map on which the action will be performed
        action - The action to be performed for each entry
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified action is null
